H3.text: Where is the Australian parliament based. Canberra

A4.text: Parliament House is located on Capital Hill in Canberra, Australian Capital Territory.

A5.text: the first Federal Parliament in Melbourne on 9 May 1901

A6.text: On 9 May 1988, a larger and permanent Parliament House was opened on Capital Hill as part of Australia's bicentenary celebrations.

A7.text: The Commonwealth Parliament moved there from the Provisional Parliament House, now known as Old Parliament House.
